{"type":"message","id":"ff715e65","parentId":"e7d6512f","timestamp":"2026-02-18T19:19:30.364Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Adjusting configurations**\n\nI’m looking to add multi-factor authentication with a pairing code. Next, I need to adjust the OpenClaw configuration via the gateway. I’ll keep my response concise by outlining the options and asking for confirmation before proceeding with any tool calls. It’s important to ensure clarity and get user buy-in on the adjustments I suggest! Let's make sure everything is set up correctly before moving forward.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"text","text":"I can help with that. Here are practical ways to restrict this chat to your account only:\n\n- Use a pairing/owner model: require a pairing approval from the bot owner for any Telegram user. Until approved, commands from others are ignored.\n- Maintain an allowlist of Telegram user IDs: only let the IDs you specify (e.g., your account 6472431299) send commands.\n- Enforce per-chat authentication: require a one-time token or passphrase per session, tied to your account, before executing sensitive actions.\n- Lock down tokens: ensure the bot token is stored securely and not usable without an approved pairing.\n\nWhat would you like me to implement here?\n- Option A: enable a strict per-user allowlist (your ID only) and block others.\n- Option B: keep a basic pairing flow (approve telegram <code>) plus allowlist.\n- Option C: something custom (specify details)."}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"auto","usage":{"input":11833,"output":619,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":12452,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1771442362588}}
